			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Looking at what damage a mage can do by casting sheds some interesting light on a problem that Kirium brought up in the "Top Ten" section, that there is basically no value to Star Strike or Ancient: Nova Strike. One can also argue that Elemental Spike and Ancient: Elemental Spike are equally flawed, but this is just about the ability to do damage, short term or long.
<br />

<br />

<br />
The issues are that under conditions where fire-based nukes land well and maximizing damage delivered to the target is of great importance:
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">
<br />
1) Star Strike and Ancient: Nova Strike provide no total damage benefit over Bolt of Jerikor when the battle is short enough that mana is not an issue.
<br />

<br />
2) If magic is landing well, even Ancient:Nova Strike provides only about a 4-5% total damage benefit over Blade Shock in 5-10 minute battles for Spec:Conj mages.
<br />

<br />
3) Star Strike and Ancient:Nova Strike provide no total damage benefit over Bolt of Jerikor for Spec: Evoc mages.
<br />

<br />
4) A Spec: Evoc mage using Bolt of Jerikor will match or surpass a Spec:Conj mage, even with Ancient: Nova Strike.
<br />
</span>
<br />

<br />

<br />
Before you suggest that Bolt of Jerikor is the problem, consider that with wizards critting over 10k regularly, an 8802 crit under the best situations generally escapes attention. (From personal experience, I have never once recieved a comment about my 8k+ crits, but the first time our wizard critted over 10k, it was widely noticed and commented on).
<br />

<br />
The problem is that Star Strike and Ancient:Nova Strike do not have any significant benefits over Bolt of Jerikor, especially when the mage choses Spec: Evoc. Only SOE's propensity for making raid mobs extremely fire resistant makes the choice of Spec: Conj attractive at this point. Presence of these mobs further trivializes any benefit that even Ancient: Nova Strike has over Blade Strike.
<br />

<br />

<br />
The following table summarizes the output of a simple model for damage (it does not discretely "cast," but takes time-average values) at what is probably "terminal" performance (which would be exceedingly likely with access to Ancient spells). No resists, fizzles, etc, are taken into account. This is merely to compare the various spells and their relative damage potential.
<br />

<br />
The data assumes a 45% magic and fire focus to 70, 
<br />
DD mana focus of 25% to 65 and 20% to 70, 
<br />
time focus of 23% to 70, 
<br />
10% spell haste buff, 
<br />
no bard, 
<br />
and the full set of applicable AAs.
<br />

<br />
Phase 1 is Heart of Flames for 90 seconds (w/ rod click)
<br />
Phase 2 is from the end of Phase 1 until mana runs out
<br />
Phase 3 is from the end of Phase 2 until 5 minutes
<br />
Phase 4 is from 5 minutes to 10 minutes (w/ rod click)
<br />

<br />
The three-letter codes across the top indicate the spell choices in order of the phases. Phase 3 and Phase 4 use the same spell.
<br />
B -- Bolt of Jerikor
<br />
S -- Blade Shock
<br />
A -- Ancient: Nova Strike
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">FOR COMPARISON PURPOSES ONLY
<br />
These overly-optimistic figures do not reflect many factors of in-game play</span>
<br />

