				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't quite get this. Magicians have always had a high damage more efficient bolt, especially moreso than even our own standard DDs.
<br />

<br />
Firebolt of Tallon:
<br />
Base Damage: 2000
<br />
Average DPS: 261.78
<br />
Base Efficiency: 4.0
<br />
Efficiency with 50 Evoc: 4.57
<br />
Efficiency with 200 Evoc: 5.0
<br />

<br />
Sun Vortex:
<br />
Base Damage: 1550
<br />
Average DPS: 217.10
<br />
Base Efficiency: 3.92
<br />
Efficiency with 50 Conj: 4.48
<br />
Efficiency with 200 Conj: 4.91
<br />

<br />
I see these OoW era nukes as mirroring prior nukes, and maintaining the balance within our nukes. Bolts have always been more efficient for Evoc-based mages than the DD's have been for Conj based mages. I see no problem with this.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
