			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I don't quite get this. Magicians have always had a high damage more efficient bolt, especially moreso than even our own standard DDs. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
And prior to OoW when those spells were designed LoS issues were a factor. That isn't the case now as its very hard to miss with the bolt.
<br />

<br />
We are losing out to every other caster class at the end game as our Ancient doesn't provide any significant gain over a mere Lvl 66 spell (this isn't even counting how much more difficult it is to get top of the line foci for Lvl 70 spells). No other class has the same situation were their Ancient Spells provide no benefit at all to them.
<br />

<br />
We already have one total joke of an Ancient and the nuke adds no power to the class. How can anyone think that this is fine? Compare to Wizards, they get a bigger, better boom nuke and a nuke thats vastly more mana efficient, we get nothing.
<br />

<br />
I can't believe even 'casual' players think its fine that the most powerful spell we get is Lvl 66 and we gain no DPS or mana efficiency by getting the higher level spells, including the Ancient spells, which should be the pinnacle of spell casting power in OoW.
<br />

<br />
Frankly I wish they'd just do away with the whole bolt idea and just concentrate all of our spells on Conjuration (we are Mages, not wizards afterall). The split spell skills just hurt us when it comes to balancing against other casters.
<br />

<br />
Alternatively shift all of our damage spells to Evoke but again lvl 70 spells must be better than lvl 66 spells regardless, with the Ancient been best of all. This is less preferable though to been all conjuration due to the other spells we get (like Pet heal, Pyrilen Skin) that are conjuration.
<br />

<br />
If they based the relation of Star Strike/Ancient Nova Strike compared to the bolt as Rock/Ancient Chaos Vortex was compared to the PoP Bolt. This would result in Star Strike doing 2345 damage with a mana efficiency that is slightly above the bolts (4.4) for a mana cost of say 525
<br />

<br />
Ancient would do 2558 damage with significantly better mana efficiency than either the bolt or StarStrike. Mana cost of around 550 would seem appropriate.
<br />

<br />
These I think are the bare minimum changes needed to the DD's now that the Bolt doesn't have LoS issues. Ideally though the Ancient should be better in every way than the bolt. That stupid second Ancient needs changing to something remotely useful aswell (pet, pet heal or BO would be better than what it currently is).<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
