				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kirium and I probably have slightly different ideas as to "how much is enough," but we're in roughly the same area.
<br />

<br />
A key point is that this is not "just for the ubers." The changes need to start with Star Strike, a spell available to all level 70 mages.
<br />

<br />
Star Strike modified to be doing 2350 damage for 485 mana would make it about 10% less DPS and 10% more efficient for a Spec:Conj mage as compared to a Spec:Evoc mage and BoJ. Such a change does not bring the mana efficiency out of line with the lower-level Blade Strike (less than 2% difference).
<br />

<br />
This is for a "modest" mage with a 25% fire focus and summoned pieces for the rest, with cleric spell haste on them, SCM3, FoM3, and QD3. The differences for the ultra-equipped and -AAed Anguish mage are virtually the same (8.5% in efficiency and 10.4% in DPS).
<br />

<br />
Ancient:Nova Strike would need to be adjusted to be an appropriate boost over that, perhaps something like 2850 damage for 530 mana, for a 10% boost in DPS over BoJ and a 10% boost in efficiency over Star Strike.  Giving the Ancient higher DPS and mana efficiency than any earlier spell has been the case with the previous Ancients.
<br />

<br />
Wizzies can breathe easy as the "magic number" for mages to break 10k crits looks to be 3216 base damage. (Ancient:Core Fire is at 4070.)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Elementalist Itchyban of Veeshan</a>
<br />
"Nothing to see here. Move along. Move along." 
<br />
"These are not the droids you are looking for."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
