				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> On some raid mobs, I find that I can land Blade Strike, Sun Vortex, and Star Strike with little or no resists--- whereas BoJ is outrright resisted.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I don't have Star Strike yet...but as far as bolts go I have a lot more resists on BoJ compared to Blade Strike.  I also had a lot more resists on FBoT compared to Sun Vortex.  One combination being fire/magic and the other fire/fire I still have tons of bolt resists either way. I noticed Sun Vortex (a 2 year old spell) resisted less than our brand new BoJ, both being fire,  as well for me before I had Blade Strike and still used SV with BoJ a bit.  I have used all three combinations (FBoT and SV - BoJ and BS - BoJ and SV) in VT, PoP and OoW raiding so it does not seem zone/mob/expansion specific...and it is not just on raid mobs that bolts seem resisted more.   This weekend alone I have taken BoJ out of my spell line up twice - once in GE soloing and once when I logged in just to kill a few green mobs in DS for Loyalist faction for 15 min only...because it just was not landing well at all.  This has happened in other zones as well, I know I have taken bolts out before in PoE and recently in RCoD xp groups.  Too frustrating, maybe I just have bad luck with bolts or hit the wrong combination of things to nuke, it is possible...no clue but bolts in general compared to DD spells resist like crazy for me.  I love them for raid mobs where mana is no issue and range fights when they decide to start landing but that is too rare compared to other nukes we have, to even consider changing spec to me.  It's even more annoying to have them start bouncing as soon as you hit HoF.  I crit for 38 with it already and have only had HoF for 2 days!
<br />

<br />
Ancients, OTOH, should be a far more superior nuke (damage and mana efficiency BOTH, imo - OR have some special factor such as unresistable) to any other in the expansion - compared to lower level spells or same level spells, or whatever else anyone can ever come up with for a Mage nuke, doesn't matter, they should be the very best and Ancient: Nova Strike just does not stand out as anything special to me.  So that I think needs work in both areas.  When I can look at it's stats and think "wow" then I will consider it an acceptable ancient.
<br />

<br />
As far as Star Strike goes (and if this ends up resisting as much as a bolt does for me I may change my mind about this spell later, atm I will consider bolts alone to be the huge resisters) I see the biggest problem being a larger issue of Mage DD spells in general...spec Evo vs. Conj.  I would not care if a bigger nuke that is resisted more comes at a lower level than one that is lower damage but less resisted.   I really would not care if they changed bolts to read Conj or DD to read Evo and keep them all doing what they currently do (aside from the ancient) but changing them all to be one or the other would vastly help the entire situation to at least START to balance out a bit, then it could be tuned more delicatly from there.  Anyhow I would rather see the larger issue of split up spec issue addressed rather than this individual spell because as it is, the spec factor seems to be a big mess and it also always seems to end up causing an imbalance (sometimes larger than other times) somewhere within the class...too bad there is no room for it on the top ten list. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Old focus effects do work better on lower level spells with the scaling now, this is true and it does give a level 66 spell (regardless of the damage) some advantage but it is only a temporary advantage.  Long term new focus effects (up to lvl 70) will slowly replace old ones as the spells remain the same.  Considering how much bolts resist (and I don't know how to measure that) and then adding on top of that spec issues I do not have a problem with BoJ on it's own being higher damage at level 66 and coming before the others.  The unknown factor with focus effects there and what amount of time the lower level spells did have that advantage from scaling thus their overall impact on a specific set of spells would be timing.  If we will go to level 80 five months from now it will obviously have a much larger effect than if we wait again two years to go up five levels to 75.<br />_________________<br /><center><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543802"><img Src ="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaFinal.jpg" border="0"></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
