			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree that the rune component make anything past Elemental Siphon basically a complete waste. The additional tick of mana regeneration isn't going to make any real difference in an XP situation and the rune makes is effectively useless for a raider (the mana regen is lost on the first AoE, it cannot be recast, and the rune is too small to be meaningful against 4k or 6k AoEs -- I have had a Shield of Auras for a long time and its rune isn't worth the buff slot).
<br />

<br />
For the mana regeneration component boost to be meaningful, the increase over Elemental Siphon has to be a reasonable percentage of about 100-120 mana/tick*
<br />

<br />
All spells should be a tangible upgrade from lower-level spells with similar effects.
<br />

<br />
Ancients should provide some boost in power that you don't need hours of parsing to see. 
<br />

<br />
Copy-n-paste from already arguably useless level 70 spells is not how to accomplish that.
<br />

<br />
I would prefer spells that had tangible and unique benefit. I'll accept ones that have a tangible benefit.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
* Raiding mana regeneration, standing:
<br />
FT 20
<br />
MC 3
<br />
Innate 3
<br />
VoC 20
<br />
Oak 9
<br />
Bard 22
<br />
Bst 10
<br />
MMM 8 (If you didn't get it in Time or GoD, its a single-group drop in OoW)
<br />
Siphon 5
<br />

<br />
Total: 100 mana/tick -- standing -- Does not include horse (19), rods, or other sources
<br />

<br />
Note further that it is no longer appropriate to include Magi`Kot's legs as a source of mana-less rods for mages as Elemental gods and Time are no longer regularly raided by all high-end mages.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Elementalist Itchyban of Veeshan</a>
<br />
"Nothing to see here. Move along. Move along." 
<br />
"These are not the droids you are looking for."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
